Ok this is my last entry in this journal want my new one? ask me...
I just have a few things to say to some people

Lauren: I'm sorry i truly am.

Lindsay: I really don't give a shit what you think of me because you don't know me.  "Manipulative dick"? then so be it i dont care.

Phil: If I'm the one your talking about on your journal, once again i don't care...in the four years of our friendship you hated the person i was becoming i know you did...you made fun of everything about me, when i was christian...some of the music i liked, the way i dressed, my bandana, my friends and so on and that got tiring.  now you hate me more than anything in this world i bet.  if you want to kill me come do itjust know that i dont give a shit enough to argue, fight with you or have any beef whatsoever because its dumb. blame me for anything and everything i dont give a shit. 

The End yay...
Ever feel completely empty.  i was driving home from golden cue tonight and a rush of some wierd ass feeling came over me. i dont know.....

I'm unhappy with everything...it's crazy...I'm so happy to be hanging with my fucking brother for the last 14 years Juan.  We celebrated nick's bday which was cool..pretty good party.  hanging out again reminds me of how fucking awesome the old skool days were well aside from the assholes from back in the day. but anywho...i just have to say a few things...
1:fuck bullshit
2:fuck that piece of shit
3:i need a break
4:new band im in kicks ass great singer and awesome beats

not so random randomness:Jesus loves you but everyone else thinks you're a fucking asshole.

So I know I haven't updated in a while but I fucked up the first semester fo college and if I didnt dso decent this semester I wouldn't have been able to go back but guess what! I'm going back i did alot better and I'm still able to go to UNF WOO HOO!  Anyhow...I'll be back to rant about something...rock on everyone I'm back for good...

THis is Fabian coming to you live from my NEW COMPUTER! 2.4 GHz pentium 4 woo! kick ass comp i must say...i call it the Jolly Roger.  Pirate style bitches.  Well I passed my first comparative religion test with a B and my first American Gov. paper with a B and my first Lit quiz with an A so take that bitches.  My crime in America test is tomorrow so wish me luck.  Anyhow I'm gonna go play some xbox then watch some monday night raw (go benoit! fuck some people up!) then im off to study but i might be back...later bitoches.

Randomness:"Sooo...sooo you think you can tell heaven from hell."

Sitting here in the library now right after my Hinduism test and I feel good about it...she repeated alot of the questions on the test..funny.  anyhow im a little tired, just passing time until my crime in america class.  once again not much new here.  cant wait to get my new computer. its gonna be so kick ass. well i dont have much more to say...very pensive lately dont know why. worried about my mom, one of her sisters died and shes going to ohio sometime soon. cant wait to get my paycheck tomorrow, got some saving to do, new tats on the way woo! hmmm got 20 more minutes till class...i miss being with lauren already :) cant wait to see her after class and sleep a little with her :)...well later everyone or no1...whoever reads this hah



Randomness: Just because I havent carried a banner that proclaimed to the entire world that I'm str8 edge and just because I havent acted like I'm better than everyone because I'm sXe doesnt mean i havent always have been.  hey maybe i think its actually ok to have some friends that arent straight edge theyre no different from anyone else who is sXe and i'm not weak and easily influenced, you dont want to fucking know the stories i have.  as for me? sXe/xXx all the way fucks. believe it or not but Fabian is straight edge.

HEy everyone yep I'm still alive...classes are going ok i guess...my crime in america class seems to be a pain in the ass but oh well. anywayz...not to much thats new from my front.  getting a new computer from my mom next week and $ from left over financial aid so thats awesome as fuck.(yes fuck can be awesome haha) my job is still awesome, as for becoming manager still undecided theres lots of pros and cons to taking the job.  getting some new tattoos soon  pirate style and hmmmmmmm not much else.  im tired and gonna go to bed soon  later...

Man...so i'm driving home from applebees with lauren and her sister and i get stopped at this safety checkpoint and get a ticket for an improperly placed tag! AHHH!  and the kicker is that a cop told me to put it in my rear window in the ifrts place! it was there cuz i couldnt get the bolts off of my tag holder thing.  its all good now i got my plate on there so i should be ok and im going to go dismiss my ticket tuesday.  well in other news...im tired and ummm yeah.  in other news good show coming up the 23rd...dont know if i want to go though...well im out later...

Randomness:Fuck off

Sooo havent updated in sometime but i love my classes this semester so far so thats kick ass...ive come to see that i love old school punk rock and metal is that so wrong?  the ramones and the clash of course...some stooges and im getting into motorhead...awesome band for their time and even still now i like it.  lots of halo goin on over here as usual and im owning. haha dont mean to toot my own horn.  might not take that promotion at work its iffy i dunno its sitll in the works i have some itme to decide.  morrowind has become my new obsession as far as video games go...very open-ended game and very very well done im only just beginning though.  still looking for hte right band...got tons of lyrics str8 from the heart written out still reluctant to show them though. oh well.  i got the new thursday cd and its awesome just like the first one.  the stuff ive been listening to though in general has been getting wider from like the roots to hardcore/emocore to old school punk and classic rock woo!  random bye...bye

Hellooooooo everyone sorry for the lack of updates ok so maybe no1 reads this but anyhow yeah xmas was great :)  lauren got me a distortion pedal i wanted for a while and i got some clothes some video games and a cd and such forth.  Got both gta's, morrowind, and moh:frontline.  theyre all fuckin awesome  im working on morrowind and vice city for now.  as for other things hmmm....saw school of rock and paycheck both very kick ass movies but the crown movie of this break has been LOTR:Return of the king...the third installment featured much action and great story and trmendous acting especially from the minor characters who indeed made the movie especially interesting. well i got the bleeding through cd....i love it even more than darkest hour but not nearly as much as norma jean woo!  got to jam on dakota's guitar while im in town and i figured i wouldve been rusty but nope fingers are moving faster and my improv is tons better...mucho new school hardcore style showing through.  welllll....been spending lots of time with lauren and thats always awesome...got to see will money and dakota and some other friends from high school.  no band thats depressing would love to play with those guys again sometime but i guess that wont happen seeing as how me n phil arent on good terms but i would like to be again.. miss the friendship but anyways...hmmmm not much else to update on  hopefully i got the manager job when i get back to hot topic and ummm.....thats all  happy new year everyone woo! for '04!

Randomness:"You're not hardcore, unless you live hardcore."---Jack Black

Oh my freakin god...soooo i finaly got to see my favorite hardcore band(Norma Jean) play wooo! They were fucking amazing from the first note...they also played a new song that was might i say awesome!  In Due Time played too and that was my second time seeing them and they were kick ass too.  Anywho  after the break i'm going to start my own hardcore band...when i went home for thanksgiving i was playing Dakota's guitar and im playing better than ive played ever.  i wrote some really kick ass breakdown/tough guy hardcore style riffs.  ive got a bunch of lyrics too. anywayz...the show was awesome i kicked ass in sales at work and oh yeah i got district employee of the month this month out of all the people who work in the 7 stores in our district so im working it...rumors are that i might get a manager(keyholder) position in january....i hope so but probably unlikely but i am doing good.  well enough tooting my own horn...cant wait to get home and get out of this fucking dorm for a little bit....well im out of here for now  later kiddies

Randomness:"A life lived in fear is a life not lived."---I heard it from $Will$(will money woo!)

Hey everyone...shaved off the blue all of it and now my hair is like UBER UBER short but thats kool.  How has the world been?  I've been pretty good actually.  Brining my amp up to school next semester im kinda psyched about that...not much new happening on my front new classes for next semester but ill update with that later  until then...adieu

Hey everyoneeeeeeeeee........back again...well ever since hanging out with lauren and working at hot topic ive gotten back into listening to incubus...now before the only cd i really ever loved by them was S.C.I.E.N.C.E. and i thought make yourself was alright and yes ill admit it...i thought morning view was crap but after listening to morning view again for real and reading its lyrics i think its absolutely genius and im falling in love with this band all over again...thanks to lauren :)...in other news...heard of linkin park,pod,hoobastank and story of the year having a show jan 10th in orlando...must go  love pod's old stuff and story of the year isnt bad at all woo for emocore poppunk typeness. (emocore represent!)  dont get me wrong tho i still love my hardcore...i hear atreyu is comin out with a new one in '04  cant wait for that one good good band...and if im on the topic of hardcore...on broken wings cd i have is decent...i got used to throwdown's singer so i like that one too but anywayz...im gonna go now tiredness and laundryness...later pookies

hey everyone...well the latest news is that me and lauren are dating :) which makes me happier than ever and i mean ever...fuck all who dont support and a big fist in the air to those who do...hmmmm this is a new experience here for me....im using a mac WHOA!...the keyboar is nice but still nothing compared to a PC with windows on it as far as O/S's go.  anywho...ive been kicking some major ass at work as far as sales associates go...ive been on the high sellers list every week since ive been there and this week alone i have a $131 sale, a $181 sale and a $105 sale.....and i have a friday night left to work  woo!  retail is my game i guess  anywho....2 bands have asked me to join em here  one is a breakdown hardcore band and the other is a metalcore band...dunno  gotta pick up my amp from home and put some new strings on myguitar...after the low E broke i tried playing without it for a bit...came up with soem cool stuff then put it down  kinda hard to write hardcore/metal with no amp   gotta know what itll sound like with distortion and all...getting some new cables too well...besides all that i got nothin haha well i did get my labret pierced and it didnt hurt at all just hurts to eat sometimes when it gets caught on your teeth but other than that it's awesome, y next venture is my straight edge tattoo on my back or some sXeness on my wrists under my stars...im considering an eyebrow piercing too but im not sure yet anywho...im outta here for now later on kiddies...

There's a bad guy comin through. Better get out of his way!"

Randomness: So what's everyone's favorite movie?  Definitly Scarface for me woo!

Look up to the sky only to tear down the stars.
We never seem to grasp an understanding of all this.
Fuck it all, take it away, bleed out my veins.
Leaving me dry.
What seemed to happen to whatever it once was?
There can't be a "just because", there has to be a reason.
Slave to emotion.
How did this change?
No one saw it from the start.
It all just turned around.
Tired of this change.
Tired of the thinking.
Tired of dying everyday.
No way to think.
Nowhere to run.
Answers are needed.

OH MY FRIGGITY GOD!!!  The Take Action show was AMAZING! Ok let's start from the beginning...Got 2 shirts a peta shirt that says question authority on it and a Poison the Well shirt with a star on it.  Ok well anywayz...Avenged Sevenfold played first and I walked in not a very big fan of theirs but after seeing them and how good they are live I'm a converted fan man they're good.  Next was my fav of the night...18 VISIONS!  Man for like 3 songs he kept putting the mic to my face to sing along AHH! I loved it!  After seeing them it got me back into listening to Vanity. <small>very good hxc cd</small>.  Then after them was Further Seems Forever...very emo not a big fan at all. <small>tear</small>.  Oh man after that was a band that kicked everyone's ass...Dillinger Escape Plan...it was the most insane band I've ever seen in my life much kudos to them for being sooooo good.  And of course to finish off the night the band I've been waiting to see for a long long while...Poison the Well.  Oh man when they played Slice Paper Wrists and Nerdy I went insane I loved it...I lost my faith in them for some time cuz their new cd kinda sucks but all is restored from such a good live show.   Kudos to all those bands.  Anywho I gotta read some english schtuff  later on everyone...
